scripts.dev:fork: cross-env NODE_ENV=development webpack-dashboard -- node -r babel-register ./node_modules/webpack/bin/webpack --config webpack.config.fork.js --progress --watch
scripts.start-hot: cross-env HOT=1 NODE_ENV=development electron -r babel-register -r babel-polyfill ./app/index.dev
scripts.build: npm run build:lib && npm run build:app && npm run build:fork
scripts.release: npm run build && npm run dist:osx && npm run dist:win
scripts.docs:publish: npm run docs:clean && npm run docs:build && cd _book && git init && git commit --allow-empty -m 'update book' && git checkout -b gh-pages && touch .nojekyll && git add . && git commit -am 'update book' && git push git@github.com:rinocloud/rinobot gh-pages --force

releases.name: Run tasks by selecting, with python, matlab and R support
releases.body:
This version for now does away with folder monitoring (don't worry it will be back!), opting instead for a file-system like UI where you can select files an run a bunch of tasks on them.
- included support for creating python snippets to work on files.
- can run matlab (and set matlabroot)
- much improved stability and performance

releases.name: Settings dropdown bugfixes
releases.body: Fixed a bug where on startup the settings menu for a new folder couldn't be seen.

releases.name: Various bugfixes for running plugins, and making custom commands
Auto-updating Rinobot
releases.body:
This version only adds the auto-updating feature to Rinobot.

It is properly signed by Apple for distribution on Mac.
It is not yet signed for windows -> you might experience a warning upon installation -> although the app itself is fine. This will be fixed in the next release or so.
